# 4. 大人の事情

Little An: Awesome! I got three at once!
Nagi: Grr...! No matter how many times I play these arcade shooters, I can never get used to them...!
An's Father: *Sigh*
An's Father: Alright, it's starting to get dark, so let's head back once those two are done playing their game.
Taiga: Sounds good. But I'm still amazed by how much energy An has after practicing all morning.
Nagi: Wait, An, don't take that weapon!
Little An: You snooze, you lose! I'm gonna take the health pack too.
Nagi: No, I needed that health pack!
Nagi: Drats, I lost again...
Nagi: An, one more time! I can't leave after that!
Little An: You really hate losing, huh, Aunt Nagi? But I like how you're not afraid to stand back up♪
Nagi: Guh... That smirk... Just who exactly are you taking after?
An's Father: Well, Nagi, you probably.
Nagi: Oops... She's copying me?
Taiga: By the way, I'm pretty good at this game.
Nagi: Shut it! I still want another go! I'll change characters this time and...
Live House Staff: E-Excuse me...! Do you all have a moment to talk?
Nagi: Hm? Oh, you're Kimura from “Ultramarine”. You seem startled. What's wrong?
Live House Staff: The thing is, we've run into a bit of trouble...
An's Father: Trouble?
Little An: ...?
Little An: (Hmm... They all look really serious...)
Little An: (This might take a while...)
Taiga: Yeah, that's not good...
Nagi: If that's the case, I'll head over. You two stay here with An.
Little An: What...?! You're leaving, Aunt Nagi?!
Nagi: Don't worry, An... We'll get to play again soon.
Little An: But I wanna play again now...
Nagi: Hehe. I know, dear. I don't like leaving after losing either.
Nagi: But right now, someone from the live house we usually perform at needs my help, so I want to be there for them...
Nagi: You'd try to help someone if you saw that they were in need, right, An?
Little An: Yeah...!
Nagi: Hehe. That's what I like to hear! And it's very cool of you, An!
Nagi: So, I'll be off... Let's play again tomorrow, An!
Little An: Oh... There she goes...
Nagi: Check this out! From downtown!
Little An: Whoa! That was awesome! You made that shot from so far away...!
Nagi: Hehe. I am pretty good at basketball. Wanna give it a try, An?
Little An: Yeah! Can I have the ball?
Nagi: First, why don't you try aiming for the backboard behind the rim? Point your toes forward and relax as you hold the ball up...
Little An: That was great! I didn't realize basketball was so much fun!
Little An: Oh, Aunt Nagi, Uncle Taiga! Wanna have dinner at our place?
Taiga: Oh, at your place? Are you sure?
An's Father: Yeah, we got some steaks as thanks from the team we helped out the other day and was thinking about grilling them up.
Nagi: Really?! Well, if you don't mind!
Little An: Yay! Mommy's really good at grilling steaks too!
Little An: Huh...?
Little An: They're constructing a really big building here! What's it gonna be?
Nagi: Oh, this sign might tell us. Let's see... It says it's going to be for “Kamiyama High School.”
Little An: Really?! This is gonna be a school?! It'd be kinda fun to go exploring♪
An's Father: An, construction sites aren't exactly safe places, so don't get too close.
Little An: Okay.
Nagi: I'm not sure you meant that at all. These sorts of places can be pretty dangerous, so please be careful, alright?
Little An: I know! It's just... I'm a little curious.
Taiga: That reminds me of how we used to sneak into school at night and stuff.
Little An: Wait, you did?
Nagi: T-Taiga! Now's really not the time!
An's Father: If anything, we were sort of forced to sneak in... If only Nagi hadn't...
Little An: Hadn't what? Aunt Nagi, did you do something bad? Why did you guys have to sneak in?
Nagi: No, I can't tell you that!
Little An: Aww... Why not...?
Nagi: I'll tell you when you're a little older! More importantly, look! We're almost home!
Little An: Yeah!
Little An: (Once we get home, we're gonna have steaks, practice singing, play games... I can't wait!)
Young Musician: Oh, um...! Pardon me for being so sudden, but do you all have a moment?
An's Father: Hm?
Nagi: Oh, I remember you. We met at that one event the other day... “Riot Party”, right? Weren't there four of you?
Young Musician: *Gasp* Yes, that's us! I can't believe you remembered us!
Young Musician: I know this coming straight out of left field... But the thing is, RADder, we need your help...
Taiga: Conversations that start like this usually don't end well in my experience...
An's Father: But for now, can you tell us what's going on?
Young Musician: We were going to sign with this one label, but we noticed today that some conflicts might arise in terms of who owns what based on what we saw in the fine print...
Young Musician: We expressed our concern because it didn't seem right, and they responded by telling us to decide whether or not to sign by the end of today.
Young Musician: Then, I heard from some people around here that RADder's probably good at dealing with these sorts of situations... Would you mind if I asked for your opinions...?
Nagi: By the end of today...? Geez, talk about being callous.
Taiga: Yeah, if this label's gonna stick it to you that much, why sign with them at all?
Young Musician: We thought that as well... But one of my teammates is going to quit if we don't land a deal this year...
Nagi: I see... If that's the case, Taiga, let's hear what he has to say.
Taiga: Ken's our best negotiator... But we're better at handling things then they go south.
Nagi: You're making me sound like some kind of ruffian. Still, I don't mind helping.
An's Father: Sorry, guys. I really appreciate it...
Little An: You guys are going, Aunt Nagi...?
Nagi: ...
Nagi: I'm sorry, An. I really want to hang out with you, but I need to go for a bit...
Nagi: We can have some yummy steaks together in the future sometime...
Little An: Okay...
Nagi: Alright, wish us luck!
Little An: Oh...
Little An: (She left again...)
An's Father: Don't worry. I'm sure you'll get to play again soon. I know. Why don't we do some singing practice together when we get back...?
Little An: Huh? Really?
An's Father: Yes, really. We can practice as much as you like.
Little An: *Gasp* Woohoo!!
